= <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> Conference

# reference: Evans, Ellen L. “Adam Stegerwald and the Role of the Christian Trade Unions in the Weimar Republic.” The Catholic Historical Review 59, no. 4 (1974): 602–26.

Wilhelm Marx, former <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> chancellor and presidential candidate, has chosen to resign from leadership of the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>. Now, the party holds a conference to replace him.

The consensus candidate on the right is Ludwig Kaas, a Catholic priest who represents the party's traditionalists. On the other hand, there is Joseph Joos, a leader of the Catholic trade unions, who has been more supportive of cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> than most of the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>. [? if not prussia_leader == "Stegerwald": Christian labor union chairman Adam Stegerwald has fallen to a distant third, making it highly unlikely that he will win the leadership.?][? if prussia_leader == "Stegerwald": Christian labor union chairman and Minister-President Adam Stegerwald has lost some ground, but he retains strong support from the Prussian branch of the party, effectively securing him the nomination. ?]

